  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

  <p>
    Fields define the structure of your data model. Each field has a name, type, and a generator
    function that produces values.
  </p>

  <h2 id="basic-fields">Basic Fields</h2>

  <p>Fields are declared in the <code>fields</code> section:</p>

  <pre set:html={`<code>model User {
  fields {
    name() string
    age() int
    email() string
    active() bool
  }

  gens {
    func name() {
      return Name()
    }

    func age() {
      return IntBetween(18, 65)
    }

    func email() {
      return Email()
    }

    func active() {
      return Bool()
    }
  }
}</code>`}></pre>

  <h3>Supported Types</h3>

  <ul>
    <li><code>string</code> - Text values</li>
    <li><code>int</code> - Integer numbers</li>
    <li><code>float</code> - Decimal numbers</li>
    <li><code>bool</code> - Boolean (true/false)</li>
    <li><code>datetime</code> - Date and time values</li>
  </ul>

